# WHAT IT IS
#   tanour is "a WASM executor for blockchains" — the Cap'n Proto RPC
#   server side of the Pactus blockchain's wasm-smart-contract execution
#   harness.  It is a long-running daemon that listens on a TCP socket,
#   speaks the Cap'n Proto two-party RPC protocol to a connecting client
#   (such as a Pactus node or a test driver), and exposes an `Executor`
#   capability defined by `tanour_capnp` (the schema is compiled at
#   build time by the `capnpc` build script into `OUT_DIR/tanour_capnp.rs`).
#   The capability lets the client load WebAssembly contract code into
#   a wasmer/wasmtime sandbox, invoke entrypoints with arguments, read
#   storage hooks, and receive gas-metered results back across the same
#   Cap'n Proto session.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from tanour-server/src/main.rs argv parsing)
#   tanour <HOST:PORT>
#
#   Positional argument:
#     <HOST:PORT>            TCP socket address to bind the Cap'n Proto
#                            RPC server on (e.g. "127.0.0.1:1234").
#                            Required — `main()` prints usage and exits
#                            cleanly if `args.len() != 2`.
#
#   Behavior:
#     - `TcpListener::bind(&addr)` opens the server socket
#     - On each accepted connection:  set `TCP_NODELAY`, split into
#       reader / writer halves, wrap in a `twoparty::VatNetwork`,
#       and hand off to `capnp_rpc::RpcSystem::new()` with the
#       `ExecutorImpl` capability bootstrap
#     - The RPC system runs on `tokio::task::LocalSet`
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependencies on BOTH `capnp` and `capnp-rpc` (pinned to the
#   canonical `capnproto/capnproto-rust` repository via git) declared in
#   `tanour-server/Cargo.toml`.  These are the two halves of the canonical
#   Rust Cap'n Proto stack:  `capnp` is the message-serialization runtime
#   (the IDL → Rust struct readers / builders generated by `capnpc`), and
#   `capnp-rpc` is the Level-2 RPC layer (capabilities, two-party vat
#   network, promise pipelining) layered on top.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/pactus-project/tanour/contents/tanour-server/Cargo.toml
#       → capnp = { git = "https://github.com/capnproto/capnproto-rust" }
#       → capnp-rpc = { git = "https://github.com/capnproto/capnproto-rust" }
#     gh api repos/pactus-project/tanour/contents/tanour-server/src/main.rs
#       → use capnp_rpc::{rpc_twoparty_capnp, twoparty, RpcSystem};
#       → let rpc_system = RpcSystem::new(Box::new(network), Some(...));
#   This entry is the Rust=121 leader bump that OPENS Axis 66
#   (Cap'n Proto RPC Library), pairing with future Go=capnproto/go-capnp
#   and TS-Node=capnp-ts / capnp-es poles to close the axis at 1/1/1.
#
#   No completion for `tanour` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_tanour() {
    _arguments \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show usage and exit]' \
        ':bind address (HOST:PORT, e.g. 127.0.0.1:1234):'
}

_tanour "$@"
